    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Swipload 3.0.0 release notes]]></title>
        <id>https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0</id>
        <link href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0"/>
        <updated>2023-11-05T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[Features]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="features">Features<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Features" title="Direct link to Features">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="shipments">Shipments<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#shipments" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Shipments" title="Direct link to Shipments">​</a></h3>
<p>Create, communicate, negotiate and get one price for multiple freight orders using a single Shipment. Order a FTL or LTL by combining multiple freight orders. A shipment can have a single or multiple pickup points and a single or multiple delivery points, and enables individual PODs for different end customers on a single shipment.</p>
<p>Shipments support the same features as regular freight orders, like:</p>
<ul>
<li>Request quote from one or many carriers</li>
<li>Send to carrier as fixed price shipment</li>
<li>Send to carrier as time &amp; material pricing</li>
<li>Communicate with carriers and drivers on a shipment</li>
<li>Share to spot market for instant resolving of your shipment need</li>
<li>Agreements, with multiple terms for your current carrier(s)</li>
<li>Integrations with ERPs and TMSs</li>
</ul>
<p>and much much more.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="photo-documentation">Photo documentation<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#photo-documentation" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Photo documentation" title="Direct link to Photo documentation">​</a></h3>
<p>When signing for pickup and/or delivery you may now attach one or more photos documenting the pickup or delivery. Photos are visible for the shipper and can be presented to the end customer.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="deviation-handling">Deviation handling<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#deviation-handling" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Deviation handling" title="Direct link to Deviation handling">​</a></h3>
<p>If a deviation occurs during the delivery process, you may now report it immediately, i.e. when signing for pickup or delivery. Attach photos to deviations for adding additional context and documentation.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="bug-fixes">Bug fixes<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#bug-fixes" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Bug fixes" title="Direct link to Bug fixes">​</a></h2>
<p>None</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="rss-feed">RSS Feed<a href="https://docs.swipload.com/release-notes/3.0.0#rss-feed" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to RSS Feed" title="Direct link to RSS Feed">​</a></h2>
